---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import MetricCard from "../../components/MetricCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <!-- HEADER -->

        <header class="mb-14">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">May 2023 — Present</p>

            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">
                FullStack Developer
            </h1>

            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                Working as a FullStack developer at
                <a
                    href="https://www.mrplan.es"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                >
                    MisterPlan S.L
                </a>, developing SaaS products in the tourism sector including
                PMS systems, Channel Managers and booking engines managing more
                than
                <strong class="text-blue-600"
                    >2 million reservations per year</strong
                >.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                My work is mainly focused on backend architecture, integrations
                and evolution of complex domain systems, while also contributing
                to the frontend when required. I work daily with PHP, MySQL,
                Docker and JavaScript within a product-oriented environment
                where scalability, reliability and maintainability are critical.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                The platform integrates with multiple third-party providers
                across different domains including distribution platforms,
                electronic invoicing administrations and smart lock systems used
                by hotels and short-term rentals.
            </p>
        </header>

        <!-- ABOUT -->

        <section class="mb-14">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">About the role</h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                I work on backend systems that support business-critical SaaS
                products used by hotels and tourism companies. The platform
                processes large amounts of reservations, billing operations and
                third-party integrations.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                My daily work focuses on evolving legacy systems towards cleaner
                architectures using principles such as SOLID, Domain Driven
                Design and Hexagonal Architecture.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- PROJECT 1 -->

        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">
                Electronic Invoicing SaaS
            </h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
                Development of a unified invoicing system that consolidates
                billing from three independent products: hotel PMS, activity
                management software and internal management systems. The module
                also implements electronic invoicing integrations for multiple
                countries and administrations.
            </p>

            <!-- METRICS -->

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-10">
                <MetricCard value="+5000" label="invoices generated per day" />

                <MetricCard value="3" label="billing domains unified" />

                <MetricCard value="6" label="electronic billing integrations" />
            </div>

            <!-- DETAILS -->

            <ul
                class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-disc pl-6"
            >
                <li>
                    TicketBai integration for the Basque Country (Araba, Bizkaia
                    and Gipuzkoa)
                </li>

                <li>VeriFactu integration for Spain</li>

                <li>SWSapien integration for Mexico</li>

                <li>
                    Architecture designed to support new regulatory integrations
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- PROJECT 2 -->

        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">
                Electronic Lock Integrations
            </h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
                Development of integrations with multiple smart lock providers
                used by hotels and short-term rental accommodations. The system
                allows automated guest access management by generating and
                distributing temporary access credentials linked to
                reservations.
            </p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-10">
                <MetricCard value="7" label="lock providers integrated" />

                <MetricCard value="+3000" label="locks managed" />

                <MetricCard value="+250" label="accommodations connected" />
            </div>

            <!-- Architecture highlight -->

            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Access abstraction model</h3>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
                Different providers expose completely different ways of granting
                access to a lock: numeric codes, temporary links, eKeys, mobile
                app permissions or provider-specific tokens.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
                To handle this variability, the system introduces an abstract
                domain entity called <strong>Key</strong>. This entity
                represents a generic access credential independently of the
                underlying provider implementation.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
                Each integration adapts its provider-specific access mechanism
                to this domain abstraction, allowing the system to support new
                providers and access types without changing the core domain
                logic.
            </p>

            <!-- Functional behaviour -->

            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Access provisioning workflow</h3>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
                The module supports two different integration strategies
                depending on the capabilities of the lock provider.
            </p>

            <ul
                class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-disc pl-6 mb-8"
            >
                <li>
                    <strong>Direct lock mapping:</strong>
                    our system maps a room to one or more locks and generates access
                    credentials directly through the provider API.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <strong>Room synchronization:</strong>
                    our system maps our room with the room entity in the provider
                    system and sends reservation information. The provider then generates
                    the required access credentials for all locks associated with
                    that room.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <!-- Technical notes -->

            <ul
                class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-disc pl-6"
            >
                <li>
                    Integrations with TTLock, Nuki, Tesa, Yacan, Padword,
                    Omnitec and Akiles
                </li>

                <li>Domain-driven abstraction for access credentials</li>

                <li>Decoupled architecture supporting multiple providers</li>

                <li>
                    Event-driven processes to ensure consistency across
                    distributed systems
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- PROJECT 3 -->

        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Activity Channel Manager</h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
                Refactoring and evolution of the activity distribution system,
                integrating major tourism distribution platforms.
            </p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-10">
                <MetricCard value="5" label="distribution platforms" />

                <MetricCard value="Millions" label="reservations processed" />

                <MetricCard value="Full" label="system refactor" />
            </div>

            <ul
                class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-disc pl-6"
            >
                <li>
                    Integrations with Civitatis, GetYourGuide, Viator, Tiqets
                    (OCTO) and Axess
                </li>

                <li>
                    Refactoring applying Clean Code and Hexagonal Architecture
                </li>

                <li>Improved maintainability and scalability</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- TECH -->

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Technologies</h2>

            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >PHP 8+</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >Laravel</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >MySQL</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >Docker</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >Vue.js</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >DDD</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >Hexagonal Architecture</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >TDD</span
                >

                <span
                    class="px-3 py-1 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm"
                    >REST / SOAP APIs</span
                >
            </div>
        </section>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
